Description:
Sophisticated street presence with space and location
Spacious two bedroom town home with study offers a flexible layout with the ultimate in convenience to Sydney Road's shopping, Trams and Moreland Station. This near new home is beautifully appointed with established garden surrounds, car parking for two cars and huge wrap around balcony to enjoy all year round. Featuring large open plan living and fully equipped chefs kitchen opening to balcony, master bedroom with walk in robe and full ensuite bathroom, 2nd bedroom with built in wardrobe, central bathroom , European laundry and study which could easily double as a third bedroom or private living space. Bathed in natural light, this home offers quality, convenience and the best of Northside living.

Description:
CONTACT AGENT TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION
We are suggesting that all buyers whether you intend on participating in the bidding, download the Anywhere Auctions App on your smart phone or tablet device which will allow you to stream and participate in the auction remotely.
Please select the link below which outlines all the important information you need to know regarding bidding registration, contract signing if you are the successful purchaser, deposits and so forth.
Link: https://anywhereauctions.com.au/how-to-bid/
Big, Bold & Beautiful
This lustrously sleek three bedroom two bathroom, double storey residence offers an ultra-modern opportunity for those who enjoy an executive lifestyle. Along with an open living and meals area, the contemporary kitchen is well equipped with state of the art stainless steel appliances including dishwasher, glass splashbacks and solid stone benches. All three spacious bedrooms contain BIRs, while the master has a lavishly black trimmed stone vanity ensuite that also matches the fully tiled central bathroom and downstairs powder room. Features include, reverse cycle heating and cooling throughout, remote garage with rear roller door access to low maintenance deck and backyard. Alarm, video intercom, OSP and all within the Strathmore Secondary College School Zone. Inspections will be sure to impress!
IMPORTANT NOTICE REGARDING COVID-19:
Please check our guidelines before attending open for inspections, auctions or our offices.
Visit: www.barryplant.com.au/media-hub/resources for the Information.
We can provide alternatives to meeting in person and for inspections, please contact us to find out what options are available to you.

Description:
Classic Style And Huge Potential
PLEASE CONTACT AGENT FOR PRIVATE APPOINTMENT
With abundant rear land, charming interiors and a flexible floor plan, this large double-fronted Federation home known as Uralla sits on the Brunswick border and presents an outstanding opportunity just waiting to be discovered. An array of options await the next owner to build upon a beautiful foundation by renovating and extending, or as a potential new home site just 9km from the CBD, moments to Citylink for city/airport access and walking distance to Sydney Road.
Substantial land spanning approx. 540sqm
Sunny north-west facing rear aspect
Spacious, well-kept period-style home
Huge scope to renovate/extend (STCA)
Minutes to Sydney Road, trains and trams
Bursting with character and elegantly reflecting its traditional origins, the current home is delightfully enjoyable as is, featuring four spacious front rooms (living plus three bedrooms or option for four bedrooms), separate kitchen and dining spaces, three original working fireplaces, high ceilings, original baltic pine floors, ducted heating throughout and established gardens with shade and fruit trees. Boasting an enviable elevated position in an attractive tree-lined street, it comes with all the advantages of wide street frontage, a deep allotment with surplus land and north-west facing rear aspect, creating exciting possibilities for those ready to embrace this opportunity.
Insights: 3 Clarendon Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2020 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Private, spacious and set to impress **Expressions of Interest Closing Thu 16th Apr 5pm**
Please Note:
To inspect this property please contact the sales agent directly to arrange a suitable time.
A private sanctuary tucked in a serene cul-de-sac, this wonderful three bedroom two bathroom residence boasts the oversized interiors and inviting courtyard gardens that families are going to love. Arranged over two light filled levels this home impresses with its huge lounge and dining, chic Blanco appointed kitchen, north-facing entertainer's deck and gardens incorporating vegetable plots, chicken coop and Japanese water feature. A second sitting room provides retreat from the everyday while grand bedrooms with robes and ceiling fans share two bright bathrooms, master with ensuite. With heating/cooling, bamboo floors, solar panels, ROW, garage plus car space, this irresistible home puts you near Moreland Station, Sydney Road trams and shops, parks, the Upfield Bike Path and schools.
Jellis Craig Coronavirus Update
If you do arrange a private inspection we ask that you support us on the following;
- A reminder to maintain healthy social distancing (at least 1.5m) from Jellis Craig sales teams
- Keeping attendees at the appointment to a minimum
- Please refrain from touching surfaces within the property where possible
We also request you refrain from attending an inspection appointment if you have:
- Tested positive to, or have symptoms associated with Coronavirus
- Recently been in contact with someone diagnosed with Coronavirus
- Recently been overseas or agreed to any self-isolation conditions
As we are no longer able to hold Auctions within the community (due to Government restrictions), this property has been converted to an Expressions of Interest campaign. If you have any interest in this property we urge you to contact us to discuss this process further.
We thank you for your understanding as we navigate through this period together.

Description:
Classic Californian with Wonderfully Wide Options!
***INSPECTION STRICTLY BY PRIOR REGISTRATION***
Moments from Merri Creek trails and parkland in one of Coburg's most tightly-held pockets, this attractive period home occupies a uniquely wide allotment (669sqm appox.) providing a lifestyle of immediate character and convenience with scope to renovate, rebuild or possibly redevelop (STCA). Behind the eternally attractive facade, discover a charming interior comprising a wide entrance hallway with original panelled walls, two main bedrooms (large master), formal dining/third bedroom and contemporary-style bathroom with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a spacious central lounge with wood heater and separate kitchen/meals area, plus the added appeal of high ornate ceilings, lead-light windows, stained timberwork and solid hardwood floors. Step outside to find an expansive backyard garden with workshop and extra-wide driveway/off-street parking emphasizing the block's impressive dimensions and untapped future potential. A prime location, it's also walking distance to Nicholson Street trams, close to primary and secondary schools as well as Sydney Road's renowned cafes and restaurants, shops, supermarkets and Coburg Station.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Single Level Convenience & Simplicity
Framed by a period woven wire fence that is so quintessentially Coburg, this welcoming three bedroom home offers easy single level accommodation, all beautifully updated with convenience in mind. With every room bathed in an abundance of natural light, step inside onto gorgeous Tasmanian Oak floors that grace the entire home. An open plan living/dining zone offers an easy space to relax and unwind whilst the stylishly spacious kitchen boasts brand new appliances (Miele oven & 900mm cooktop, Bosch dishwasher). Clever under bench lighting illuminates expansive stone benches, providing ample space to cook up favourites as you effortlessly entertain, whilst the waterfall island offers a comfortable spot for family and friends to linger and chat. The bathroom has been totally transformed to offer you the perfect place to pamper, whilst the modern laundry offers practical functionality and storage options. Each bedroom also offers built in robes. Your privacy and security is assured, with your driveway and remote-controlled garage directly accessing the easy care rear garden and courtyard. Gas ducted heating and split system air conditioning offer year round comfort. Whether you're a first home buyer starting out, a family, a downsizer or simply looking for a low maintenance lifestyle, this move in ready home offers you your perfect next step. In one of Coburg's best pockets, walk to local primary schools (Coburg West & St Fidelis) whilst local parks, cafes, Sydney Road shopping, public transport and the Freeway are all within easy reach.
In conjunction with: Wendy Chamberlain

Description:
Vast and versatile family home
Please Note:
To inspect this property please contact the sales agent directly to arrange a suitable time.
Vast and impressive this five bedroom plus study, three bathroom family home also includes a ground floor self-contained unit ideally suited to extended families. Versatility and space go hand in hand to provide an array of formal and informal living spaces for all. Enjoy large bedrooms, master with ensuite and balcony access, roomy bathrooms and plenty of space for a couple of study areas. Virtually maintenance free the large backyard also has potential for a rear right of way. Extras include, four car garage plus off street parking, ample laundry facilities, alarm, marble staircase, front and rear balconies, ducted heating and wall furnace. With something for everyone, it is extremely close to parklands, schools, Bell Street transport and Sydney Road shops/cafes.
Jellis Craig Coronavirus Update
Please note some key changes to our open for inspection processes as we continue to work through the current Coronavirus situation;
- A reminder to maintain healthy social distancing (at least 1.5m) from anyone else attending the open for inspection, including the Jellis Craig sales teams
- Please refrain from touching surfaces within the property where possible
- You may be requested to wait outside the property to help reduce the number of people in the property at the one time
We also request you refrain from attending an open for inspection if you have:
- Tested positive to, or have symptoms associated with Coronavirus
- Recently been in contact with someone diagnosed with Coronavirus
- Recently been overseas or agreed to any self-isolation conditions
If you are unable to attend the property but are still interested, please contact the agent and they will advise you of the best way to proceed.
Thank you for your understanding as we work through this situation together

Description:
Versatile Style and Parkland Views
***'inspection strictly by prior registration' ***
Location Perfection! Tucked away in a secluded cul-de-sac overlooking the open spaces of Campbell Reserve, this two-storey home delivers a low-maintenance lifestyle of quality, privacy and flexibility. Idyllic inner-urban living or blue-chip investing, this home is perfect either way comprising three bedrooms (large master) all with built-in robes, spotless two-way bathroom along with two separate WCs (one on each level). Add to this a light-filled open living/dining area accompanied by an updated kitchen complete with stainless steel cooking appliances and Bosch dishwasher. Other stand-out features include ducted heating and split-system air conditioning (both levels), new carpets, solid hardwood floors, full-size laundry and under-stair storeroom with trapdoor to more storage space under the home. Step outside to discover a sunny north-facing backyard with extensive paving and established perimeter gardens for added privacy, plus an internally-accessed garage (currently converted to a carpeted study/home office) and additional driveway parking space. Moments from Merri Creek trails, it also offers easy access to cafes and schools, local shops and IGA supermarket, an endless array of restaurants as well as Moreland Road buses and a choice of tramlines to university/hospital precincts and the CBD.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Grand Slam Potential in Coburg's Heartland
On a vast corner allotment complete with its own tennis court, this extraordinary period home provides an outstanding inner-urban family lifestyle with every Coburg advantage along with a myriad of options for those looking to extend or possibly sub-divide and develop (STCA). Retaining all its authentic grandeur and superb craftsmanship, the home's remarkable interior showcases a wonderfully wide entrance hallway with ornate wood panelling, four spacious bedrooms (extra-large master) and spotless central bathroom. Add to this an impressive formal lounge with feature bay window and double doors through to the adjoining dining room, light-filled family/meals area and timber-cabinet kitchen with dishwasher and gas cooktop. Other remarkable features include high ornate ceilings and solid hardwood floors, original internal doors and stained timberwork, open fireplaces with intricate brickwork, as well as a laundry with second shower and additional WC. Step outside to a north-facing backyard with large undercover patio, garage via side driveway and second garage directly onto Wellington Street, plus the remains of a full-size tennis court highlighting the property's vast dimensions and untapped potential. The best of Coburg at your fingertips, it's walking distance to Coburg Station, Sydney Road trams, cafes and restaurants, boutique shops and major supermarkets, as well as easy access to local parks and schools. Game, set and match!
Land Size: 34m x 35m =1195sqm Approximately
Inspections by Appointment.

Description:
Picture Of Sustainable Sophistication
Superbly renovated with an eye on sustainability, this stunning five bedroom two bathroom Californian Bungalow home is set to impress. Meticulously finished, showcasing high-end appointments and double glazing through a north-facing extension, this home hits a high point with its modern open plan design. A spacious AEG/Miele island kitchen with WIP and stacker doors to an entertainer deck and gardens presents seamless entertaining, while floorplan versatility comes via a retreat and studio space/home gym. Excellence continues through designer bathrooms, hydronic heating, cooling, hardwood floors, plantation shutters, solar panels and drive through garage with remote and internal access. In a south of Bell locale, it boasts schools, Nicholson Street and Sydney Road cafes, trams and Merri Creek parklands within walking distance.

Description:
A Quality home ready for you to enjoy
Enjoy the confidence of a quality construction by APC build a 2019 master builders association award winner. Well designed for family living and perfect for those looking to upsize, get into the market or secure a future investment with previous returns of $800 per week. Not matter which way you look at it, this home is sure to impress.
A family home featuring four bedrooms each with generous built in robes and the master enjoying a walk in robe and ensuite. Three bathrooms with each level having access to a bathroom ensures peaceful family living especially on those mornings when everyone is rushing to get ready. This home also boasts two living areas with a formal lounge/living greeting you as you enter the front door and complimented by the large open plan living/kitchen area. The kitchen is a masterpiece with SMEG appliances and a well-positioned island bench perfect for those who enjoy preparing a meal and conversing with family and friends.
Flowing on from the open plan living is the rear courtyard. With space for the kids to play or invite some friends over for a BBQ it's yours to enjoy. With a single car garage, a tandem open space and security system you will have peace of mind knowing your home and possessions are safe and secure. Some extra features include double glazed windows, fully networked cat 6 data ports, refrigerated ducted heating & cooling, window shutters, full insulation and sound proofing. There's nothing more to do but move in and enjoy.
Perfectly positioned for those who like to be central to everything. With tram route 1 and multiple bus routes within walking distance getting around to explore your surroundings couldn't be easier. A short drive will have you at Sydney Road where you will find a plethora of specialty restaurants, cafes and shops. An immediate walk will have you at Harding Street where you'll find some of the best hidden cafes and take away shops. For those who enjoy the outdoors you have the Merri Creek trail almost in your backyard and De Chene Reserve. Excellent schools are also close by such as Antonine College and Coburg high school.

Description:
Elegant entertainer in an exciting lifestyle locale
A north-facing rear entertainers' garden with decking, highlights the exciting easy living emphasis of this elegant 3 bedroom home with broad frontage to Salisbury Street. Set beyond landscaped garden with off-street parking and internal remote-control garage, this superbly renovated residence offers beautifully presented and balanced interior spaces exuding excellent quality and graceful style in an easy-care, inner-city location. Close to a series of local cafes, enhance the lifestyle allure of a great location close to Sydney Road, trams, train station, parks and schools. Featuring ducted heating, reverse-cycle air-conditioning, decorative ceilings, stained glass windows and polished Jarrah floors, this attractive home includes three large bedrooms with built-in robes, spacious living room with cosy wood heater, dining area, large granite kitchen with stainless-steel appliances, delightful bathroom, laundry with second shower. An outstanding single-storey haven that's low on upkeep while high on quality.

Description:
Quintessential Character with Modern Family Flair
***Inspection Strictly By Prior Registration***
On a substantial high-side block with enviably easy access to the best of Coburg, this gorgeous Victorian displays all the elements of its period heritage along with quality enhancements and an expanded floorplan to deliver an outstanding inner-urban family lifestyle. Immediately alluring with its picket-fenced garden, decked verandah and elegant facade, the home's immaculate interior comprises a wonderfully wide central hallway, three large bedrooms (two with BIRs), spotless bathroom and separate WC. Add to this a spacious lounge leading through to the open dining/living area complemented by a superb modern kitchen with stone benchtops/breakfast bar, soft-close cabinetry, dual Fisher & Paykel dish drawers, Bosch oven and induction cooktop. Towering ceilings with ornate plasterwork and solid timber floors add to the appeal, along with ducted heating, evaporative cooling, split-system air conditioning, gas-coal fireplace (lounge) and a full-size internal laundry. Step outside to discover a delightfully deep backyard complete with undercover entertaining deck, established gardens, handy storage shed and off-street parking via remote-control rollerdoor to ROW. A prime location walking distance to Nicholson Street trams, Merri Creek trails and acres of parkland, it's also close to primary and secondary schools as well as Sydney Road's renowned cafes and restaurants, shops, supermarkets and Coburg Station.
